# wait-until-headers.tflw — CHECK-ONLY FIXTURE (M5): a `header` line attached under `wait until
# api` — the parse-time proof behind TFLW-FEATURE-GAPS.md #3 ("`wait until api` cannot carry
# per-step headers"). `parseWaitUntilApi` (testFlow/packages/lang/src/parser.ts) never calls
# `parseApiHeaders()` the way `parseApiStep` does, so this never parses at all — TF010, "only
# `expect` lines may follow `wait until api`, found `header`". See tests/jobs.tflw and
# tests/token-expiry.tflw for the real working scenarios this forces (the latter's whole reason
# for existing is that a header-carrying poll here isn't an option).
#
# Run explicitly (dot-directory, invalid syntax — see tests/.checkonly/bad-keyword.tflw's header
# for why):
#   npx tflw check tests/.checkonly/wait-until-headers.tflw

test "a header line under wait until api"
  wait until api GET /jobs/abc-123
    header "Authorization" is "Bearer sometoken"
    expect body.status equals "completed"
